{"word":"intellegere","priority":"☆☆☆","meanings":[{"part_of_speech":"verb","definition":"(ラテン語) 理解する、知る、悟る、気づく、解釈する","english_definition":"(Latin) to understand, comprehend, know, perceive, realize, interpret","examples":[{"sentence":"Difficile est intellegere quid dicis.","translation":"あなたの言っていることを理解するのは難しい。","english_translation":"It is difficult to understand what you are saying."},{"sentence":"Intellegere debes quid agendum sit.","translation":"何をすべきか理解しなければならない。","english_translation":"You must understand what must be done."},{"sentence":"Intellexi te adesse.","translation":"あなたがそこにいることに気づいた。","english_translation":"I realized you were there."}],"collocations":["intellegere veritatem (真実を理解する)","intellegere sententiam (文を解釈する)","intellegere signum (兆候を理解する)"],"synonyms":["cognoscere","scire","percipere","animadvertere"],"antonyms":["ignorare","nescire"]}],"etymology":{"value":"ラテン語の「inter」（間に）+「legere」（選ぶ、読む）から。元々は「選り分ける」「見分ける」といった意味合いがあり、それが転じて「理解する」という意味になった。","priority":"★★☆"},"pronunciation":{"ipa":"/inˈtɛlːɛɡɛrɛ/","syllables":"in-tel-le-ge-re"},"inflection":{"verb_forms":{"present_infinitive":"intellegere","perfect_infinitive":"intellexisse","present_active_indicative":{"1st_person_singular":"intellegō","2nd_person_singular":"intellegis","3rd_person_singular":"intellegit","1st_person_plural":"intellegimus","2nd_person_plural":"intellegitis","3rd_person_plural":"intellegunt"},"imperfect_active_indicative":{"1st_person_singular":"intellegēbam","2nd_person_singular":"intellegēbās","3rd_person_singular":"intellegēbat","1st_person_plural":"intellegēbāmus","2nd_person_plural":"intellegēbātis","3rd_person_plural":"intellegēbant"},"future_active_indicative":{"1st_person_singular":"intellegam","2nd_person_singular":"intelleges","3rd_person_singular":"intelleget","1st_person_plural":"intellegēmus","2nd_person_plural":"intellegētis","3rd_person_plural":"intellegent"},"perfect_active_indicative":{"1st_person_singular":"intellexī","2nd_person_singular":"intellexistī"